Anh - Anh
Dard
[dα:d]
■ noun
1》 a member of a group of peoples inhabiting eastern Afghanistan, northern Pakistan, and Kashmir.
2》 the Indic languages spoken by the Dards.
Derivatives
Dardicnoun & adjective
Origin
the name in Dard.
